`<http://198.211.98.156/dev/generate/url>` will process a job, even if the URL is crazy, like:

```
{
	"url" : "<https://af.wordpress.dfdorg>"
}
```

That returns this:

```
{
    "jobID": "480"
}
```

Ideally, it would return a message in the format of `/generate/sitemap/`. Something like this:

```
{
    "jobs": [],
    "messages": [
        "No single page found, looking at <https://af.wordpress.dfdorg>",
    ]
}
```

Note: `"jobs"` and `"messages"` are also presented here as an array. Even though only one job could be returned from `/generate/url`, it would make integrating various endpoints easier if we made the output uniform across endpoints.
